
[1]abroad

   ABROAD, adv. abrawd'. [See Broad]

   In a general sense, at large; widely; not confined to narrow limits.
   Hence,

   1. In the open air.

   2. Beyond or out of the walls of a house, as to walk abroad.

   3. Beyond the limits of a camp. Deut. xxiii. 10

   4. Beyond the bounds of a country; in foreign countries - as to go
   abroad for an education. We have broils at home and enemies abroad.

   5. Extensively; before the public at large.

   He began to blaze abroad the matter. Mark i. 45.

   Esther i.

   6. Widely; with expansion; as a tree spreads its branches abroad.
